<li>Description of the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://hyperphysics.phy-astr.gsu.edu/hbase/audio/tape.html">recording process</a> with diagrams. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://hyperphysics.phy-astr.gsu.edu/hbase/audio/tape2.html">pg. 2</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://hyperphysics.phy-astr.gsu.edu/hbase/audio/tape3.html">pg. 3</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://hyperphysics.phy-astr.gsu.edu/hbase/audio/tape4.html">pg. 4</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://hyperphysics.phy-astr.gsu.edu/hbase/audio/tape5.html">pg. 5</a>.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://rfwilmut.net/broadcast/recording.html">Recording at the BBC</a> – a brief history of various sound recording methods used by the BBC.</li></ul>
